author: gstein
msg: Align the datatypes and variable names with the underlying needs.
- follow the command line switches: no_unlock instead of remove_lock, and
keep_changelist, rather than remove_changelist. note the logic reversal
- use a hash for the dav-cache rather than an array of changes
* subversion/libsvn_wc/adm_ops.c:
(committed_queue_item_t): keep the ADM_ABSPATH rather than the whole
access baton. flip the lock/changelist booleans. store the dav-cache
as a hash
(process_committed_leaf): alter the params, per above. remove the
wcprops conversion code, since the caller already gives us the hash
(process_committed_internal): alter the params, per above. flow them
through the sub-calls. make sure to reverse the logic for passing
a NO_UNLOCK constant to the sub-calls
(convert_to_hash): ripped out of process_committed_leaf to convert an
old-style array of wcprop changes into a dav-cache hash.
(svn_wc_queue_committed2): store the altered values into the item
(have_recursive_parent): remove the unused pool argument
(svn_wc_process_committed_queue): adjust for changes in the item
structure.
(svn_wc_process_committed4): convert the wcprops to a hash, and reverse
the logic on the remove_* params.

author: blair
msg: Default argument clarification.
* tools/dev/count-wc-ng.py
(print_report):
Do not have a default argument for wc_root.
Always pass a value to print_report().  Do not use a default value
otherwise the reader has to look in two places to see what
print_report() is using.
